TODO: tap0 creation

./x86_64-softmmu/qemu-system-x86_64 -bios OVMF.fd -device rtl8139,netdev=tap0,bootindex=1,mac=52:54:00:12:34:57 -netdev tap,id=tap0,ifname=tap0,script=no

dhcpd should listen to a bridge interface or to an interface whose other end belong to the bridge.
Listening to tap0 directly doesn't work.

brctl addbr br0
brctl addif br0 tap0

Minimal config for isc-dhcp-server:

subnet 192.168.2.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 {
}

host LocalQemu {
	hardware ethernet 52:54:00:12:34:57;
	fixed-address 192.168.2.1;
	next-server 192.168.2.254;
	filename "/efi64/syslinux.efi";
}

atftpd is configured on the command line directly.
In my case, it's started by inetd in /etc/inetd.conf

tftp		dgram	udp6	wait	nobody /usr/sbin/tcpd /usr/sbin/in.tftpd --tftpd-timeout 300 --retry-timeout 5 --maxthread 100 --verbose=5 /srv/tftp

Change /srv/tftp if needed.
Or set /srv/tftp/efi64 as a symbolic link to the efi64 directory where you compiled syslinux. For instance /home/celelibi/code/syslinux/efi64.
